Hi ChihFeng,

This is a part of our feature highlight series. A few tips to help you get =
the most out of Scrintal!

Feature highlight: The alignment tool =F0=9F=93=8F

We know working on a canvas can be a stream-of-consciousness kind of thing.=
 You take notes, write down ideas and create new documents. But you still w=
ant to keep it neat and organised.

> This is when the alignment tool is really useful.

It can look a bit intimidating with its many symbols, but don=E2=80=99t wor=
ry. In this email, we will cover all of the alignment options, and what the=
y do.

=F0=9F=A5=87 Top tip

Let's start with something that shows what knowing the alignment tools allo=
ws you to do.

You get the best out of the tools when you combine them. E.g. the horizonta=
l distribution and top alignment:

[Content Library Image]

How the different alignments work

Now, let's cover each alignment tool separately.

=F0=9F=91=88 Align left
Aligns the left side of the selected items to the leftmost item.

[Content Library Image]

=F0=9F=91=89Align right
Aligns the right side of the selected items to the rightmost item.

[Content Library Image]

=E2=98=9D=EF=B8=8F Align top
Aligns the top of the selected items to the highest placed item.

[Content Library Image]

=F0=9F=AB=B5 Center horizontally
The selected items meet in the middle around a common center.

[Content Library Image]

=E2=86=94=EF=B8=8F Distribute horizontally
Distributes the selected items with equal distance from each other. All ite=
ms will be evenly distributed horizontally, following the leftmost item.

[Content Library Image]

=E2=9D=93What about vertical distribution?
The best way to vertically align elements is to stack them on top of each o=
ther. This way, the layout will not break even as you keep adding text.

[Content Library Image]

We hope you=E2=80=99ve found this short guide helpful, and that you try it =
out yourself today if you haven't already!

Until next time,
Ece & the team


